- Orders over $1000 refer to orders where the total amount exceeds $1000;
- "Beginning of 2022" refers to the start of the year 2022, i.e., January 1, 2022;
- "Most recent order" is determined by the latest order date for each customer.

- 'significant wave' refers to a total amount of 100.0 or more;
- 'ebb and flow of the 'Loyalty Program' campaign' refers to the payment date falling within the start and end dates of the 'Loyalty Program' marketing campaign;
- 'only the first ripple is needed' refers to the `LIMIT 1` clause in the SQL query.

- "big spenders" refers to customers whose total spend is greater than the average spend across all customers;
- "outshone the average" means their spending is above the average;
- "from the brightest to the dimmest" indicates the results are ordered by total spend in descending order.

- "showered the most gold" refers to customers who have spent the most money;
- "in the last half-year" refers to the last 6 months;
- "actively placing orders" refers to customers who have placed orders in the last 3 months.

- "Loyal customers" are those who have spent more than $1000 on orders since January 1, 2022;
- "Perfect rating" refers to a rating of 5;
- "Loyalty programs" are marketing campaigns specifically targeted at loyal customers with a budget greater than $5000.

- "Total order value" refers to the sum of all order amounts for a customer;
- "Total payment value" refers to the sum of all payments made by a customer;
- "Good credit reports" and "poor credit reports" are status categories in the credit reports table;
- "Average total order value" is the mean of the total order values for all customers.

- High-value customers are defined as those who have spent more than $1000 in total;
- Positive spending history means they have spent more than $0;
- High ratings are considered to be greater than 4 on a scale;
- Good credit scores are those above 600.

- "Most valuable customers" refers to customers with the highest total order value;
- "Stars in the galaxy of your business" is a metaphor for the most important or influential customers;
- "Total spending" is the sum of all order amounts for each customer;
- "Feedback" includes the number of feedback entries and the average rating given by each customer;
- "Creditworthiness" is determined by the most recent credit score.

sql:
SELECT MAX(total_spent) AS highest_total_spent
FROM (
  SELECT customer_id, SUM(total_amount) AS total_spent
  FROM orders
  GROUP BY customer_id
) AS customer_totals;

external_knowledge:
- "shone brightly in their purchases" refers to customers who have placed orders in the past year (2023) with completed status;
- "bestowed the highest ratings on their orders" refers to customers with the highest average ratings in the `customer_feedback` table;
- "the past year" refers to the period between January 1, 2023, and December 31, 2023.

sql:
SELECT MAX(total_purchase_amount) AS highest_total_purchase
FROM (
    SELECT customer_id, SUM(total_amount) AS total_purchase_amount
    FROM orders
    GROUP BY customer_id
) AS customer_totals;

